 constrain the upper limit of CO$_2$ relative abundance provided\nthe slit-projected area on the coma is larger than the collisional zone. If a\ncomet has equal abundances of CO$_2$ and H$_2$O, then the red-doublet emission\nis significantly ($\\sim$50%) controlled by CO$_2$ photodissociation and thus\nthe G/R ratio is not suitable for estimating CO$_2$ relative abundance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 May 2014 10:28:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
